  <dsc><c01 id="aspace_41c027414c27c0fa10a82433d23651fc" level="series"><did><unittitle>Series I. Project Corona Harvest</unittitle></did><scopecontent id="aspace_f0dbcfc6e9fa105c2fd5779551bf89c5"><head>Scope and Contents</head><p>System to evaluate the effectiveness of airpower in Southeast Asia, encompassing all airpower employed from 1954 to the end of the conflict (Air Force project).</p></scopecontent><c02 id="aspace_b95da259d28b02bc1cc3be32d4666926" level="file"><did><unittitle>Operating instructions,</unittitle><unitdate calendar="gregorian" era="ce" normal="1968/1968">1968</unitdate><container id="aspace_8c20aeb0c1da3c19719c110c514e1239" label="Mixed Materials [31924065231767]" type="box">1</container><container id="aspace_9b5acefcfbe12fa5ef7da0354866f56c" parent="aspace_8c20aeb0c1da3c19719c110c514e1239" type="folder">1</container></did></c02></c01><c01 id="aspace_31b3f9ce3ef62b93de0f164052166b79" level="series"><did><unittitle>Series II. HES 70</unittitle></did><scopecontent id="aspace_e88a6bcd02d8872d77949ad7609419ba"><head>Scope and Contents</head><p>Hamlet Evaluation System--reporting system designed to gather data on the progress of the rural pacification effort.</p><p> Data gathering instrument--formatted, multiple choice questionnaire:</p><list numeration="arabic" type="ordered"><item>Respondent--U.S. advisors in the field</item><item>Sample size--Every inhabited hamlet and village in south Vietnam</item><item>Frequency of reporting--Every hamlet and village reported each month</item></list></scopecontent><c02 id="aspace_a81aa771bd08d080b11d65ef3cae9121" level="file"><did><unittitle>Comparison of HES 70 and PAAS</unittitle><container id="aspace_98fa2ab82cae1383e8204fdab6d0f84c" label="Mixed Materials [31924065231767]" type="box">1</container><container id="aspace_4d3cd03449cd22767b014c2619e3fe10" parent="aspace_98fa2ab82cae1383e8204fdab6d0f84c" type="folder">2</container></did></c02><c02 id="aspace_6453be361f1413a120189c68cbfe112e" level="file"><did><unittitle>Memo,</unittitle><unitdate calendar="gregorian" era="ce" normal="1970/1970">1970</unitdate><container id="aspace_3ebfd77c73d91687ca32bb68d03e2af7" label="Mixed Materials [31924065231767]" type="box">1</container><container id="aspace_fafe1fee0aa501b4fd97cd941b79d591" parent="aspace_3ebfd77c73d91687ca32bb68d03e2af7" type="folder">3</container></did></c02><c02 id="aspace_63f443526d2bd5d2834dd1219b6f0999" level="file"><did><unittitle>Appendix A--Question codes, question responses</unittitle><container id="aspace_b9aaae75b8963c1a200a9dd27f7526f2" label="Mixed Materials [31924065231767]" type="box">1</container><container id="aspace_a9779ddc7fa30452f581c8d3aba313c8" parent="aspace_b9aaae75b8963c1a200a9dd27f7526f2" type="folder">4</container></did></c02><c02 id="aspace_d6b4471d53763cfc200aaa638bf82279" level="file"><did><unittitle>Hamlet level HES statistics and plots by NMCSSC for village program analysis (1)</unittitle><container id="aspace_03b977f73e4bd56d6afdfa53190d1cce" label="Mixed Materials [31924065231767]" type="box">1</container><container id="aspace_4702ad3070dd2caab40b762d3beb5674" parent="aspace_03b977f73e4bd56d6afdfa53190d1cce" type="folder">5</container></did></c02><c02 id="aspace_30e1ddc9fbe4713f5fdedb372974cd5e" level="file"><did><unittitle>VSSG IDX (2)</unittitle><container id="aspace_e167b7c84824b6b50cc42793765b2a71" label="Mixed Materials [31924065231767]" type="box">1</container><container id="aspace_7c945ba8d205223012eee8279eb1d518" parent="aspace_e167b7c84824b6b50cc42793765b2a71" type="folder">6</container></did></c02><c02 id="aspace_edc01af99883551698a8ec98e68e01d3" level="file"><did><unittitle>Security (3)</unittitle><container id="aspace_eb9b223e34fa9b56cd8b93460fc61f34" label="Mixed Materials [31924065231767]" type="box">1</container><container id="aspace_6ffa15f8a12971d5e126013734a5e671" parent="aspace_eb9b223e34fa9b56cd8b93460fc61f34" type="folder">7</container></did></c02><c02 id="aspace_3f069b0239082094f76d405a36d5b790" level="fil